      "span_text": "The hyperbolic regions of the Eulerian field will have an impact on the Lagrangian dynamics only if the time evolution, as measured by the velocity of the stagnation points and the deformation rate of the streamlines around them, is not too fast.  Figure 3 shows that the Eulerian hyperbolic stagnation points move slowly through the flow field, since they make only half a rotation in the time that the vorticity peaks make a complete rotation around the middle point ͑see frames a-e͒."
